

  Q2. What are the Spring Stereotype annotations, and what are the main uses of these annotations.
  
  Answer)  There is total 4 types of Stereotype Annotations :- 
  
  
			1. Component :- Component is a parent of all the Annotations. If we not able to decide in which layer this class will be stored than 
			                we can write component.
			                
			2. Repository :- Repository means that class is belongs to data access layer.
			
			3. Service :- Service means that class is belongs to business logic layer where we can write business logic related method.
			
			4. Controller :- Controller means we have to apply this annotation on presentation layer classes.
			
		 
			
			 
			
			
			
			
  